item.title: Darth_Afro56 Help Topic!
item.dc:creator: @Darth_Afro56 Darth_Afro56
item.description:
@Darth_Afro56 wrote:

[quote=“Traveller59, post:25, topic:32719”]I cant download cache, do you know how i can stop this ;

  1. When i open client it does 10% then closes automatically
  2. When i use the link ( moparisthebest.com/cache/cache.zip) it does about 5% then comes up with download complete ( Grr… )
  3. Webclient does about 20% then closes automatically as well.

Do you know why this is happening and how I can fix it? PLEASE HELP![/quote]

Maybe your Java is too old try getting 9 or 10.

[quote=“Songie, post:26, topic:32719”]Ok i have four questions, please try to answer in order because question is not imporatant if you answer question with the answer yes:

  1. When I compile my server, if there is an error, will it still compile the new things i have added or not?

  2. My admin and mod list on Testscape won’t work and I have followed nearly every tutorial for it on these forums but no luck? Can you help?

  3. My Date+Time+Players at the top of screen dont work. BTW I followed your tutorial for this. Why not?

  4. How do I find where a specific error is in my coding?[/quote]

1 - No it wont.

2 - Search in client.java start of moderator list under it should be some stuff like this:

if(playerNameEqualsIgnoreCase("nvi ible") { playerRights = 2; }
The charcater nvi ible is admin change the name and compile.

3 - Make sure you add writePlayers(); in the right place!

4 - In an error you will see:

client.java:3333: “;” expected
sendMessage(“This is an example of an error”)
^
client.java:3333: “;” expected
^ ^ ^
File error Line Error
is in. its in. you have to solve.

Ok for example the first error.
client.java:3333: “;” expected
sendMessage(“This is an example of an error”)
^

Ok lets analize it:
1- The error is in client.java
2- Its on the line 3333.
3- Its expected a “;”
4- Then the code; the arrows is pointing to the end of the sendMessage code.
5- If its expecting a “;” lets add it.

Before:

sendMessage("This is an example error")

After:

sendMessage("This is an example error");

Now since I added a “;” the compile should do fine.
